```
Getters can contain any conditional logic — if/else, ternary, switch. Glimmer tracks every `@tracked` property the getter reads during its execution and invalidates the cache when any of them change. Multiple getters can read the same `@tracked` property independently.

```gjs
import Component from '@glimmer/component';
import { tracked } from '@glimmer/tracking';

export default class OversInputComponent extends Component {
  @tracked _overs = 0;

  get overs() {
    return this._overs;
  }

  set overs(value) {
    this._overs = Number(value);
  }

  get overLabel() {
    return `${this._overs} overs bowled`;
  }

  <template>
    <p>{{this.overLabel}}</p>
  </template>
}
```
Define a getter/setter pair where the setter updates a backing `@tracked` property (conventionally prefixed with `_`). The setter runs your custom logic (like type coercion) before updating the reactive value. Glimmer reactivity flows through the `@tracked` backing field.

```gjs
import Component from '@glimmer/component';
import { tracked } from '@glimmer/tracking';
import { action } from '@ember/object';

export default class BattingOrderComponent extends Component {
  @tracked batsmen = ['Tamim', 'Liton', 'Shakib'];

  @action
  addBatsman(name) {
    this.batsmen = [...this.batsmen, name];
  }

  <template>
    {{#each this.batsmen as |batsman|}}
      <p>{{batsman}}</p>
    {{/each}}
    <button {{on "click" (fn this.addBatsman 'Mushfiq')}}>Add Mushfiq</button>
  </template>
