    return list.sort((a, b) => {
      const aVal = a[this.sortField] ?? 0;
      const bVal = b[this.sortField] ?? 0;
      if (typeof aVal === 'string') {
        return this.sortAscending ? aVal.localeCompare(bVal) : bVal.localeCompare(aVal);
      }
      return this.sortAscending ? aVal - bVal : bVal - aVal;
    });
  }

  <template>
    {{#each this.sortedBatsmen as |batsman index|}}
      <tr>
        <td>{{index}}</td>
        <td>{{batsman.name}}</td>
        <td>{{batsman.runs}}</td>
      </tr>
    {{/each}}
  </template>
}
```
Handle both numeric and string field sorting by checking `typeof` inside the sort comparator. Spread the array before sorting to avoid mutating the original. The getter re-runs whenever `sortField`, `sortAscending`, or `this.args.batsmen` changes.

